<Base title="Impulse Workshops" description="Impulse workshops for hands-on understanding of Shopware strategies and topics – Hob by Horse.">
<div class="lp"><section class="hero"><div class="hi">
<p class="kicker">Strategy</p>
<h1>Impulse Workshops for Hands-On Understanding of Shopware Strategies</h1>
<p>Setting impulses means motivating people to make changes through idea stimulation. Regarding your online shop, it is about conveying the diversity of Shopware features in a short time in a practically relevant way to your company. Impulse workshops are brief, efficient and immediately applicable in e-commerce depending on the business model.</p>
</div></section>
<div class="content">
<h2>Impulse Workshops on Shopware by Hob by Horse</h2>
<p>Impulse workshops are training sessions on a specific technology – in our business, on the features of Shopware 6. They aim to explain the theoretically offered features quickly and efficiently to users, developers and experts like Hob by Horse. The provider Shopware itself provides impulses in its training sessions, webinars and YouTube tutorials. Our task is to convey this knowledge in a way that exactly meets the challenges you face in your individual online shop.</p>
<h2>Detailed Content Examples in Impulse Workshops for Three Groups</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>User, Developer and Developer Advanced Training:</strong> For users, Shopware 6 offers step-by-step training on configurations after initial installation. Developer training can benefit your IT staff who may already have basic experience with Shopware 6. We completed the Advanced Training ourselves before being certified as a Silver Partner.</li>
<li><strong>Template and Advanced Template Training:</strong> Design professionals from the shop system explain how templates can be created and modified. The advanced version is aimed at IT specialists with basic experience in templates.</li>
<li><strong>Practical tips in B2B User Experience webinars:</strong> Here you receive impulses for customer needs in B2B, which in e-commerce practice are unfortunately still viewed too closely to those in the B2C business. You learn new purchasing processes for an optimal user experience of specialist customers.</li>
<li><strong>Shopware 6 and ERP:</strong> We attended webinars on Pickware in Shopware 6 and the possibilities for online shops of all sizes and industries, and use this compact knowledge for e-commerce developments for our customers.</li>
<li><strong>Shopware Flow Builder:</strong> In this one-hour webinar, you learn important facts about automations for better process optimisation of business processes in your online shop.</li>
</ul>
<h2>Impulse Workshops for IT Users of All Industries and Business Models</h2>
<p>When you want to update or expand a running online shop in practice, your IT staff don't always need the full load of feature experience, but rather more user tips on the details that are urgently needed right now. Therefore, our impulse workshops are tailored not only to specific industries, but within these areas to different business models.</p>
<h2>Benefits of Impulse Workshops by Hob by Horse for Your Target Groups</h2>
<p>B2B target groups are rightly regarded as specialist customers. However, the shop presentations for them are often cumbersome, too vaguely presented and thus barely distinguishable from other online shops with the same or similar offerings. Such strategic details are of course also advantageous for your B2C target groups, because they are offered a trendy user experience that sets your business model apart from competitors.</p>
<p><em>Looking for impulse workshops to get practical tips instead of theoretical grey areas? Call Hob by Horse or describe your current learning topic in an <a href="mailto:info@hob-by-horse.de">email</a>!</em></p>
</div></div>
</Base>
